text: Monchazy () is a rural locality (a village) in Okhlebininsky Selsoviet, Iglinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 168 as of 2010. There are 3 streets. == Geography == It is located 42 km from Iglino, 3 km from Okhlebinino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Iglinsky District
title: Monchazy
